<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  USB devices this app will be offered for on attach (android.hardware.usb.action.USB_DEVICE_ATTACHED).
  Attaching a matching device raises the "Open Vyooo?" dialog, which also grants USB permission — the
  grant whose absence produces SDK error 2002 ("CHECK_TYPE status timeout").

  Ported verbatim from the Insta360 SDK's own filter: sdkcamera-1.10.1 AAR → res/xml/device_filter.xml
  (referenced by the SDK demo's AndroidManifest.xml:61-63). This app-level copy overrides the library
  resource of the same name so extra vendor/product ids can be added without patching the AAR.

  ⚠️ UNVERIFIED FOR THE INSTA360 X4 AIR (the client's camera). These two entries are all the SDK
  ships, and we have only an X4 locally. If a client's X4 Air enumerates with a different VID/PID it
  will NOT match this filter (no attach dialog) — the in-app pre-flight in Insta360UsbManager still
  requests permission, so connecting keeps working, but the attach-time grant is lost.
  To confirm: attach the camera to the client's phone and read logcat tag `Insta360Usb` — every
  attached device is logged as `vid=0x… pid=0x…`. Add the reported values below.
-->
<resources>
    <usb-device vendor-id="0x2e1a" product-id="0x2" />
    <usb-device vendor-id="0x4255" />
</resources>
